laboratory_examinations.findings: Subject 1: 19.9 IU/liter (higher than normal but not postmenopausal); Subject 2: 26.2 IU/liter; Subject 3: 20.4 IU/liter.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Subject 1: FSH increased to postmenopausal range over time; Subject 2's FSH rose to postmenopausal range 1.5 years after presentation (maximum FSH, 63.1 IU/liter); Subject 3's FSH rose to postmenopausal range 17 months after initial presentation.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Subject 1: 42 IU/liter; Subject 2: 49.1 IU/liter; Subject 3: 92.5 IU/liter (all elevated above postmenopausal range).
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: LH levels were elevated throughout the observation period.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Subject 1: maximum of 112 pg/ml (411 pmol/liter) in cycle 1, 135 pg/ml (495 pmol/liter) in cycle 2; Subject 3: 74 pg/ml; Subject 2: below the limit of detection.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Estradiol levels did not increase in cycle 3 in Subject 1; remained low despite multiple dominant follicles.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Subject 1: 3- to 6-fold higher than the upper normal limit (mean: 173 pg/ml) during cycles; Subject 2: 2- to 5-fold above the upper limit; Subject 3: at the upper limit.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Inhibin B levels remained elevated across cycles.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Subjects 1 and 2: levels were in the normal range.
Levels were below the lower limit of normal in all subjects.
Subject 2: within normal limits despite multiple dominant follicles.
